ck]], better known as \"The Hippo\"\n* [[KKHK]] 95.5\t[[Adult Hits]], better known as \"Bob-FM\"\n* [[KWAV]] 96.9 [[Adult Contemporary]], better known as \"The Wave\"\n\n===Redding, California===\n* [[KQMS (AM)|KQMS]] 1670 News Talk 1670 Simulcast on 104.9 K285FE (Redding) & 105.7 K289BT (Anderson)\n* [[KSHA]] 104.3 [[Adult Contemporary]] better known as \"K-Shasta\"  \n* [[KWLZ]] 99.3 [[Contemporary Hit Radio|CHR]], better known as \"Wild 99-3\" \n* [[KRRX]] 106.1 [[Active Rock]] better known as \"106X\" \n* [[KNRO]] 1400 [[Sports Radio|Sports Talk]] better known as \"Fox Sports\" Simulcast on 103.9 K280GP (Redding)\n* [[KRDG]] 105.3 [[Classic Hits]]\n\n==Oregon==\n===Medford, Oregon===\n* [[KTMT (AM)|KTMT]] 580 [[Sports Radio|Sports Talk]], better known as \"The Game\"\n* [[KTMT-FM]] 93.7 [[Contemporary Hit Radio|CHR]], better known as \"NOW-FM\"\n* [[KBOY-FM]] 95.7 [[Classic Rock]]\n* [[KCMX (AM)|KCMX]] 880 [[News/Talk]]\n* [[KCMX-FM]] 101.9 [[Adult Contemporary]], better known as \"Lite 102\"\n* [[KAKT]] 105.1 [[Country music|Country]], better known as \"The Wolf\"\n\n==Washington==\t\t\t\t\n===Spokane, Washington===\n* [[KBBD]] 103.9 [[Adult Hits]], better known as \"Bob-FM\"\n* [[KDRK-FM]] 93.7 [[Country music|Country]], better known as \"The Mountain\"\n* [[KEYF-FM]] 101.1 Classic Hits\n* [[KGA]] 1510 [[Sports Radio|Sports talk]] and [[Hip-Hop|Hip-Hop Music]], Better known as \"103.5 The Game\", Simulcast on 103.5 K278CY (Spokane)\n* [[KJRB]] 790 [[Classic Rock]], better known as \"94.1 The Bear\", Simulcast on 94.1 K231CU (Spokane)\n* [[KZBD]] 105.7 [[Contemporary Hit Radio|CHR]], better known as \"NOW-FM\"\n\n===Tri-Cities, Washington=== \n*[[KUJ-FM|KUJ]] 99.1 FM [[Contemporary Hit Radio|CHR]], better known as \"Power 99.1\"\n*[[KIOK]] 94.9FM [[Country music|Country]], better known as \"The Wolf\"\n*[[KEGX]] 106.5FM [[Classic Rock]], better known as \"The Eagle\"\n*[[KKSR]] 95.7FM [[Contemporary Christian Music|Christian Music]], better known as \"Shine\"\n*[[KALE]] 960AM [[Adult Contemporary]], better known a \"106.1 More FM\", Simulcast on 106.1 K291BS (Richland)\n*[[KJOX (AM)|KJOX]] 1340AM [[Sports radio|sports talk]], ESPN Radio\n\n===Yakima, Washington===\n*[[KARY]] 100.9 FM Classic Hits, better known as \"Cherry FM\"\n*[[KBBO (AM)|KBBO]]  1390 AM is a [[Sports radio|sports talk]] station, better known as \"The Fan\", Simulcast on 104.5 K283BX (Wapato)\n*[[KHHK]] 99.7 FM [[Contemporary Hit Radio|Rhythmic-CHR]], better known as \"Hot 99.7\"\n*[[KTCR]] 980 AM [[Oldies]], better known as \"Kruzn 106.9 KTCR\", Simulcast on 106.9 K295BT (Wapato)\n*[[KRSE]] 105.7FM [[Classic Rock]], better known as \"The Hawk\"\n*[[KXDD (FM)|KXDD]] 104.1FM [[Country music|Country]], better known as \"KX-Double-D\"\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Radio broadcasting companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Tulsa, Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:2008 establishments in Oklahoma]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the Las Vegas newspaper publisher|Stephens Media}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name            = Stephens Media Group\n| logo            =\n| type            = [[Private company|Private]]\n| founded         = 2008\n| industry        = [[Mass media]]\n| location        = [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]]\n| key_people      =\n| products        = [[Radio broadcasting]]\n| homepage        = {{url|https://smgok.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Stephens Media Group''' is an [[Oklahoma]] based [[radio broadcaster]] that owns 75 radio stations particularly in small to mid-size markets. Its flagship stations are at its headquarters in Tulsa.<ref>https://www.linkedin.com/in/davidstephenstulsa</ref><ref>https://radioinsight.com/headlines/105667/stephens-media-acquires-four-in-ardmore-ok/</ref> Stephens refers to itself as \"A portfolio of People\", referencing the listeners of their stations.\n\n==History==\nStephens Media started with stations around [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]], before expanding to small markets outside of there.\n\nOn May 1, 2008, Stephens Media announced that it would acquire WFKL, WRMM-FM, and WZNE in [[Rochester, New York]], as a part of [[Entercom]]'s purchase of stations from [[CBS Radio]] in the market.<ref>[http://www.radioink.com/HeadlineEntry.asp?hid=141970&pt=todaysnews Entercom Sells Three In Rochester, NY] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081211132800/http://www.radioink.com/HeadlineEntry.asp?hid=141970&pt=todaysnews |date=2008-12-11 }} - ''Radio Ink'' (May 1, 2008)</ref>\n\nIn April 2018, Ingstad Radio sold 14 of its stations in Washington to Stephens Media Group.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/175389/stephens-media-group-buys-14-ingstad-yakima-tri-ci|title=Stephens Media Group Buys 14 Ingstad Yakima, Tri-Cities Stations|website=All Access|language=en|access-date=2019-09-04}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, it was announced that the company would acquire 37 stations from [[Mapleton Communications]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://radioinsight.com/headlines/178504/stephens-media-group-acquires-37-stations-from-mapleton-communications/|title=Stephens Media Group Acquires 37 Stations From Mapleton Communications|date=2019-07-05|website=RadioInsight|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-04}}</ref> This acquisition  was approved on October 9, 2019, <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rbr.com/stephens-completes-its-mapleton-deal/|title=Stephens completes its Mapleton deal|date=9 October 2019|publisher=Streamline Publishing|access-date=19 October 2019}}</ref> and was completed on October 15, 2019.\n\n==Radio stations==\n{{list|date= March 2020}}\n==Oklahoma==\n===Tulsa, Oklahoma (Flagship)=== \n*[[KTSO]] 100.9 [[1980s_in_music|80s Hits]], better known as \"Totally Awesome 80s\" \n*[[KXOJ-FM]] 94.1 [[Contemporary Christian Music|Christian Music]]\n*[[KCFO]] 970 [[Christian Radio|Christian Talk]]\n*[[KMYZ-FM]] 104.5 [[Alternative Rock|Alternative]], better known as \"Z104.5 The Edge\"\n*[[KYAL (AM)|KYAL]] 1550 [[Sports Radio|Sports Talk]], better known as \"The Animal\" Simulcast on 99.9 K260CR (Sapulpa)\n*[[KYAL-FM]] 97.1 [[Sports Radio|Sports Talk]], better known as \"The Animal\"\n\n===Ardmore, Oklahoma===\n*[[KKAJ-FM]] 95.7 [[Country music|Country]], better known as \"Texoma Country\"\n*[[KTRX]] 92.7 [[Active Rock]]\n*[[KVSO]] 1240 [[Sports Radio|Sports Talk]], simulcast on 107.5 K298CR (Ardmore)\n*[[KYNZ]] 107.1[[Classic Hits]], better known as \"GTO 107\"\n\n==New York==\n===Massena, New York===\n*[[WRCD]] 101.5 [[Classic Rock]], better known as \"The Fox\"\n*[[WVLF]] 96.1 [[Adult Contemporary]], better known as \"The Mix\"\n*[[WMSA]] 1340 [[News/Talk]]\n\n===Ogdensburg, New York===\n*[[WNCQ-FM|WNCQ]] 102.1 [[Country music|Country]], better known as \"Q-Country\"\n*[[WPAC (FM)|WPAC]] 98.7 [[Oldies]], better known as \"Pac-FM\"\n*[[WYSX]] 96.7 [[Contemporary Hit Radio|CHR]], better known as \"Yes-FM\"\n\n===Rochester, New York===\n*[[WFKL]] 93.3 [[Adult Hits]], better known as \"The Fickle\"\n*[[WRMM]] 101.3 [[Adult Contemporary]], better known as \"Warm 101.3\"\n*[[WZNE]] 94.1[[Alternative Rock|Alternative]], better known as \"The Zone\"\n\n===Watertown, New York===\n*[[WCIZ]] 93.3 [[Classic Hits]], better known as \"Z93\"\n*[[WFRY]] 97.5 [[Country music|Country]], better known as \"Froggy\"\n*[[WNER]] 1410 [[Sports Radio|Sports Talk]], better known as \"FOX Sports Radio\"\n*[[WTNY]] 790  [[News/Talk]]\n==Louisiana==\n===Alexandria, Louisiana===\n* [[KLAA-FM|KLAA]] 103.5 [[Country music|Country]], better known as \"LA 103.5\"\n* [[KEZP]] 104.3 [[Christian Music|Christian Adult Contemporary]], better known as \"The Bridge\"\n* [[KBKK]] 105.5 [[Country music|Classic Country]], better known as \"K-Buck\"\n* [[KEDG]] 106.9 [[Adult contemporary]], better known as \"Sunny 106.9\"\n\n===Monroe, Louisiana===\n* [[KMYY]] 92.3 [[Country music|Country]], better known as \"The Wolf\"\n* [[KNNW]] 103.1 [[Contemporary Hit Radio|CHR]], better known as \"Now\"\n* [[KXRR]] 106.1 [[Mainstream Rock|Rock]], better known as \"Rock 106\"\n* [[KZRZ]] 